      "modified": "1970-01-01T00:00:00.025Z",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "value": "**Second paragraph.** The line-end effect is visible across both paragraphs: certain glyphs cluster at line endings (notably the \"-y\" terminal) and others at line beginnings. This positional asymmetry, measurable across the full corpus, is the strongest single statistical argument for genuine language — random cipher noise wouldn't produce it.",
          "purpose": "commenting"
        }
      ],
